ADR-0001 — Atlas Platform Architecture

Title

Atlas Platform Architecture
Context

Atlas is intended to become an intelligent self-hosted media platform rather than a collection of independent containers.

Decision

Project Atlas shall be organized into modular subsystems:

Media Platform
Operational CLI
Atlas Retention Intelligence (ARI)
Documentation
Automation

Each subsystem owns a single responsibility.

Consequences

Benefits:

Easier maintenance
Easier testing
Easier expansion

Tradeoffs:

Slightly more documentation
More modular code

Status:

Accepted



ADR-0002 — Atlas Retention Intelligence Architecture
Context

Operational reporting grew beyond simple snapshot collection.

Decision

ARI is divided into four independent engines:

Health
Analytics
Forecast
Recommendations

Each engine performs one responsibility.

Consequences

Benefits

Smaller functions
Easier debugging
Easier future expansion

Status

Accepted


ADR-0003 — Immutable Snapshot Architecture
Context

Operational history should never be modified.

Decision

Snapshots are immutable.

Each collection creates a new snapshot.

Reports always compare snapshots.

Consequences

Benefits

Historical accuracy
Auditing
Trend analysis
Forecasting

Status

Accepted


ADR-0004 — Runtime State Architecture
Context

ARI engines needed to share calculated values.

Decision

Forecast and Health publish runtime state.

Recommendation Engine consumes runtime state.

Consequences

Benefits

No duplicate calculations
Cleaner architecture
Easier dashboard integration

Status

Accepted


ADR-0005 — Docker Networking
Context

Download traffic must remain inside the VPN.

Decision

qBittorrent shares the Gluetun network namespace.

All download traffic exits through VPN.

Consequences

Benefits

Privacy
Simpler networking
Automatic kill switch

Status

Accepted



